法規內容.條文內容:
In applying for establishment registration, the applicant shall submit the following documents:
1. The application form;
2. The identification document of the responsible person; in the case of partnership, the identification documents of the partners and the partnership agreement;
3. The certificate of capital;
4. The ownership certificate of the building where the business is located; in the case that the owner is not the responsible person of the business or a partner, the written consent of the owner shall be attached. The ownership certificate of the building can be substituted by the transcript of the building, the tax registration proof of the building, the most recent building tax statement or other documents which can prove the owner of the building. The written consent of the owner can be substituted by the lease agreement signed between the business and the owner or the lease agreement signed between the business responsible person and the owner specifying that the building can be used for business registration or for business use.
In the case that the capital of the business is less than NTD 250,000, the applicant is exempted from submitting the document of item 3 in the preceding paragraph.

In the case of business transfer, the transferee shall apply for the transfer registration by submitting the following documents:
1.the application form;
2.the transfer agreement; and
3.the identification document of the responsible person; in the case of partnership, the written consents of the partners or the partnership agreement shall also be submitted;

In the case of business succession, the applicant shall submit the following documents:
1. the application form;
2. the genealogical list of succession;
3. the succession agreement;
4. in the case of partnership, the partnership agreement;
5. if applied by the guardian, the certificate of guardianship shall be submitted; if applied by the administrator of estate, the certificate of administrator of estate shall be submitted;
6. the certificate of tax paid issued by tax authorities, the certificate of transfer consent issued by tax authorities, and the certificate of tax exemption or the certificate of exclusion from the gross estate; and
7. other documents supporting the succession.
The applicant applies for registration prescribed in the preceding paragraph by a final court judgment, the documents of Item 2 and Item 3 in the preceding paragraph can be replaced by such court judgment.

In applying for the appointment, removal or transfer of a managerial officer, the applicant shall apply for registration of the appointment, removal or transfer by submitting the following documents:
1.the application form;
2.the relevant supporting documents regarding the appointment, removal or transfer of the managerial officer;
3.the identification document of the managerial officer; in the case of partnership, the written consents of the partners shall also be submitted.

A business branch, which established separate accounting books, shall apply for the establishment registration by submitting the following documents:
1. The application form;
2. The documents supporting the mandate of the managerial officer of the branch and the identification document of the managerial officer; in the case of partnership, the written consents of the partners shall also be submitted;
3. The ownership certificate of the building where the branch is located; in the case that the owner is not the responsible person of the business or a partner, the written consent of the owner shall be attached. The ownership certificate of the building can be substituted by the transcript of the building, the tax registration proof of the building, the most recent building tax statement or other documents which can prove the owner of the building. The written consent of the owner can be substituted by the lease agreement signed between the business and the owner or the lease agreement signed between the business responsible person and the owner specifying that the building can be used for business registration or for business use.

If any change in the particulars of registration of the business branches, an application for amendment to the registration shall be filed by submitting the following documents:
1.the application form;
2.the certificate of the amendment; in the case of partnership, the written consents of the partners shall also be submitted.
